5. Call-to-Action (CTA) Section Copy
5.1 Prompt Used
🎯 CTA Section Prompt
PROMPT:
You are a conversion copywriter for a professional cafe/restaurant website. Write 3 different CTA sections for "The Golden Brew" in Hyderabad. Each CTA should have: (1) A short punchy headline (max 10 words), (2) A supporting line (max 20 words), and (3) A button label (3–5 words). CTAs should target: booking a table, contacting for catering, and following on social media. Tone: professional and trustworthy. No fluff.
AI OUTPUT:
CTA 1 – Table Booking
Headline: Reserve Your Table in Under a Minute
Supporting: Skip the wait. Secure your preferred time slot with an easy online booking.
Button: Book a Table Now

CTA 2 – Catering Enquiry
Headline: Catering for Events, Done Right
Supporting: Planning a corporate lunch or private event? Our team handles everything — from setup to service.
Button: Enquire About Catering

CTA 3 – Social Media
Headline: Follow Our Journey, One Dish at a Time
Supporting: Behind-the-scenes, new arrivals, and daily specials — all on our Instagram.
Button: Follow Us on Instagram

5.2 Final CTA Copy

📅 Table Booking
Reserve Your Table in Under a Minute
Skip the wait. Secure your preferred time slot with an easy online booking.
[ Book a Table Now ]	🍱 Catering Enquiry
